snippet.title: 193 | Flirting With The Concept That Support Is Sexy With Elayne Fluker
snippet.description:
Full Show Notes: https://AmberDeLaGarza.com/193 
======================================================
Whenever you’re ready, here are four great ways to improve your time management and elevate your productivity:

#1 Grab my FREE Take Back Your Time Mini Training | https://AmberDeLaGarza.com/TakeBackYourTime 

#2 Get instant on-demand access to my Conquer Your Email Masterclass | https://AmberDeLaGarza.com/ConquerYourEmail 

#3 Get my 4-module, on-demand training program Time Management Made Simple | https://AmberDeLaGarza.com/Time

#4 Join my group coaching + training + accountability experience Leverage Lab | https://AmberDeLaGarza.com/LeverageLab/

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
Website |  https://AmberDeLaGarza.com
Podcast |  https://AmberDeLaGarza.com/podcast
Listen on Apple Podcasts | https://AmberDeLaGarza.com/applepodcast
Facebook |  https://www.facebook.com/theproductivityspecialist/ 
Instagram | https://www.instagram.com/amber_delagarza/ 
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

I sit down with author, podcast host, and founder of SiS.Academy, Elayne Fluker, to dive into her mission to help unapologetically ambitious women get over what she calls, “I Got It” Syndrome, embrace support, and know that having it all doesn't mean doing it all alone.

 What You’ll Discover In This Episode:

 ✔ The 3 Reasons We Push Back Against Support

 ✔ How To Overcome “I’ve Got It” Syndrome

 ✔ What It Means To Live Your Question

 ✔ How To Take Advantage Of HELP

 ✔ Eye-Opening Ways You Can Ask For Support

 ✔ So Much More!
